HEADWORD: Tritiated
<hw>Trit"i*at*ed</hw> <pr>(tr⟦icr⟧t"⟦icr⟧*⟦amac⟧t*⟦ecr⟧d)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>containing <er>tritium</er>; -- of
chemical compounds; <as>as, <ex>tritiated</ex> thymine</as>.</def>
<note>Compounds which are <ex>tritiated</ex> are, as a consequence,
radioactive, and may be used as tracers in biochemical or chemical
analysis.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

